We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

Student Council Fundraiser- Our Mission for Pennies for Patients Begins Now
Warriors, I am excited to announce that we have officially kicked off our Pennies for Patients program today!

Last year we raised over $2,500 and this year we plan to raise more! Students will be coming home with their own collection box and a flyer that explains all of the exciting Hero Gear students can receive by collecting money in their box. This year, we are also encouraging students to set up an online page to receive donations, so that our school can make our biggest impact ever for the Mission of LLS. post_text: Today Warrendale kicked off March Reading Month with our first guest reader that is very well know by many in the Warrendale Community! We were honored to have Senator Sylvia Santana read one of her favorite books to our 1st grade students. Students enjoyed Senator Santana's entertaining reading of "Grace for President" by Kelly Dipucchio. Students enjoyed asking questions and expressing their future goals of becoming president. A few members of Student Council were happy to escort Senator Santana during her visit. We look for Senator Santana's future visits and assisting with upcoming community projects.
